title: Highest Percentage of Terrestrial Protected Areas
description: In 2024, Seychelles had 68.1% of its total land area designated as terrestrial protected areas, showcasing its commitment to conservation and environmental protection.

title: 100% Newborns Protected Against Tetanus
description: As of 2023, Seychelles achieved a remarkable milestone with 100% of newborns being protected against tetanus, reflecting the country's strong healthcare initiatives.

title: Lowest Aquaculture Production
description: In 2017, Seychelles reported an aquaculture production of just 0.1 metric tons, indicating minimal activity in this sector.

title: Minimal Net Official Aid Received
description: Seychelles received $50,000 in net official aid in 2021, one of the lowest amounts globally, suggesting limited reliance on foreign aid.

title: Minimal Aid from Sweden
description: In 2017, Seychelles received $9,999.99 in net bilateral aid from Sweden, marking it as one of the lowest recipients of Swedish aid.
